# Frappe client scripts: custom form events

When sharing logic between the main DocType form and child-table handlers (or between several parent field hooks), **prefer custom events** registered on the parent DocType over top-level standalone functions.

1. Register a named handler on the main form with `frappe.ui.form.on("Parent DocType", { ... })`. The key does **not** need to match a DocField — any string works (e.g. `update_total_amount`).
2. Invoke it with `frm.trigger("event_name")` from parent field hooks, child table hooks, or other code that has the parent `frm`.

```javascript
frappe.ui.form.on("Ride Booking", {
	update_total_amount(frm) {
		// shared logic
	},
	rate(frm) {
		frm.trigger("update_total_amount");
	},
});

frappe.ui.form.on("Ride Booking Item", {
	distance(frm) {
		frm.trigger("update_total_amount");
	},
});
```

Use standalone file-level functions only when the logic is not naturally owned by the form controller (e.g. pure utilities with no `frm`).
